defaultSuccessive governments seem to have been reluctant to implement this for the electrical industry
default but 5 year assessment of individuals need not be any 
defaultmore onerous than annual a
defaultssessment of enterprises.
default2.5.0default              defaultthe effect of competition between accreditation bodies, and the two separate registers of electricians, on the standards of review of domestic electrical work;default default2.5.1
default              
defaultIt was abundantly clear from the video of the meeting 
defaultthat entrusting a registration scheme to competing bodies is not the way forward. Each body 
defaultrelies on being slightly different from its competitors in order to secure an advantage over the other. This is not the right atmosphere in which to develop common 
defaultstandards, particularly where safety is concerned.
default2.5.2
default              
defaultI have watched with interest over many years how bodies which claim to be maintaining standards are actually responsible for distorting them or at least “muddying the waters.” Electrical test certifi
defaultcates are a case in point. BS7671 provides model forms for certification of ele
defaultctrical installations but, most bodies 
defaultand trade association
defaults have
default produced their own version of the form. This is very confusing when encouraging people to “conform to the stan
defaultdards” when the very bodies responsible for policing them encourage the use of non-standard documents.
default2
default.
default5.3
default              
defaultThe chairman was right, the only way to cut through the vested interests and enforce standardization is to impose a statutory registration body.
